</p><p><b>Terry Alan Crews</b> (born July 30, 1968) is an American actor and former <a href="/wiki/National_Football_League" title="National Football League">NFL</a> player. He is perhaps best known for playing <a href="/w/index.php?title=List_of_Everybody_Hates_Chris_characters&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="List of Everybody Hates Chris characters (page does not exist)">Julius</a> on the <a href="/wiki/UPN" title="UPN">UPN</a>/<a href="/w/index.php?title=The_CW_Television_Network&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="The CW Television Network (page does not exist)">CW</a> sitcom <i><a href="/wiki/Everybody_Hates_Chris" title="Everybody Hates Chris">Everybody Hates Chris</a></i> and for his appearances in <a href="/wiki/Old_Spice" title="Old Spice">Old Spice</a> commercials,<sup id="cite_ref-expendables_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-expendables-1">[1]</a></sup> <i><a href="/wiki/Arrested_Development_(TV_series)" title="Arrested Development (TV series)">Arrested Development</a></i>, <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=The_Newsroom_(U.S._TV_series)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="The Newsroom (U.S. TV series) (page does not exist)">The Newsroom</a></i> and for his roles in films like <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Friday_After_Next&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Friday After Next (page does not exist)">Friday After Next</a></i>, <i><a href="/wiki/White_Chicks" title="White Chicks">White Chicks</a></i>, <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Bridesmaids&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Bridesmaids (page does not exist)">Bridesmaids</a></i>, <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Idiocracy&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Idiocracy (page does not exist)">Idiocracy</a></i>, <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Gamer_(film)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Gamer (film) (page does not exist)">Gamer</a></i>, and <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=The_Expendables_(2010_film)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="The Expendables (2010 film) (page does not exist)">The Expendables</a></i>. He has starred as Nick Kingston-Persons in the <a href="/w/index.php?title=TBS_(TV_channel)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="TBS (TV channel) (page does not exist)">TBS</a> sitcom <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Are_We_There_Yet%3F_(TV_series)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Are We There Yet? Currently he plays NYPD Sergeant Terry Jeffords on the <a href="/wiki/Fox_Broadcasting_Company" title="Fox Broadcasting Company">Fox</a> sitcom <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Brooklyn_Nine-Nine&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Brooklyn Nine-Nine (page does not exist)">Brooklyn Nine-Nine</a></i>.

<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Early_life_and_education">Early life and education</span></h2>
<p>Crews was born in <a href="/wiki/Flint,_Michigan" title="Flint, Michigan">Flint, Michigan</a> on July 30, 1968,<sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2">[2]</a></sup> the son of Patricia and Terry Crews, Sr.<sup id="cite_ref-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-3">[3]</a></sup> Crews grew up in a strict <a href="/w/index.php?title=Christian&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Christian (page does not exist)">Christian</a> household where the rearing of the children was mainly held down by his mother. After earning his high school diploma from Flint Academy, he received a Chrysler-sponsored art scholarship at the prestigious <a href="/wiki/Interlochen_Center_for_the_Arts" title="Interlochen Center for the Arts">Interlochen Center for the Arts</a> in Northern Michigan. This achievement was soon followed by an equally impressive Art Excellence scholarship and a full-ride athletic scholarship for football at Western Michigan University in Kalamazoo. As a defensive end for the WMU Broncos, Crews earned All-Conference honors and helped his team win the <a href="/wiki/Mid-American_Conference" title="Mid-American Conference">Mid-American Conference</a> Championship in 1988. Crews was drafted by the <a href="/w/index.php?title=St._Louis_Rams&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="St. Louis Rams (page does not exist)">Los Angeles Rams</a> in the 11th round of the <a href="/w/index.php?title=1991_NFL_Draft&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="1991 NFL Draft (page does not exist)">1991 NFL Draft</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-terrycrewsdraft_4-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-terrycrewsdraft-4">[4]</a></sup> His career included stints with the Rams, <a href="/wiki/San_Diego_Chargers" title="San Diego Chargers">San Diego Chargers</a>, the <a href="/wiki/Washington_Redskins" title="Washington Redskins">Washington Redskins</a> and the <a href="/wiki/Philadelphia_Eagles" title="Philadelphia Eagles">Philadelphia Eagles</a>.
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Career">Career</span></h2>
<p>After retiring from the NFL in 1997, Crews pursued an acting career and got a role as T-Money on <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Battle_Dome&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Battle Dome (page does not exist)">Battle Dome</a></i> (modeled after <i><a href="/wiki/American_Gladiators" title="American Gladiators">American Gladiators</a></i>). Crews played the <a href="/wiki/Beefcake" title="Beefcake">beefcake</a> "he-man" in films such as <i><a href="/wiki/White_Chicks" title="White Chicks">White Chicks</a></i>. He played Damon Pearly in <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Friday_After_Next&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Friday After Next (page does not exist)">Friday After Next</a></i>, starring <a href="/wiki/Ice_Cube" title="Ice Cube">Ice Cube</a> and <a href="/wiki/Mike_Epps" title="Mike Epps">Mike Epps</a>. He has also done commercials with <a href="/w/index.php?title=Nike,_Inc.&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Nike, Inc. (page does not exist)">Nike</a>. He last starred in the <a href="/w/index.php?title=Situation_comedy&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Situation comedy (page does not exist)">sitcom</a> <i><a href="/wiki/Everybody_Hates_Chris" title="Everybody Hates Chris">Everybody Hates Chris</a></i> as <a href="/w/index.php?title=List_of_Everybody_Hates_Chris_characters&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="List of Everybody Hates Chris characters (page does not exist)">Julius Rock</a>, and his more modern movie appearances were alongside <a href="/wiki/Adam_Sandler" title="Adam Sandler">Adam Sandler</a> in <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=The_Longest_Yard_(2005_film)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="The Longest Yard (2005 film) (page does not exist)">The Longest Yard</a>,</i> <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Click_(2006_film)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Click (2006 film) (page does not exist)">Click</a></i>, and <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=The_Benchwarmers&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="The Benchwarmers (page does not exist)">The Benchwarmers</a></i> (as well as the long-delayed <a href="/wiki/Mike_Judge" title="Mike Judge">Mike Judge</a> film <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Idiocracy&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Idiocracy (page does not exist)">Idiocracy</a>,</i> where Crews played President Dwayne Elizondo Mountain Dew Herbert Camacho).
</p><p>Crews has made many cameo appearances. He was in <a href="/w/index.php?title=Blink-182&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Blink-182 (page does not exist)">Blink-182</a>'s music video of "<a href="/w/index.php?title=Down_(Blink-182_song)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Down (Blink-182 song) (page does not exist)">Down</a>" as a police officer, in <a href="/wiki/Jamie_Kennedy" title="Jamie Kennedy">Jamie Kennedy</a>'s "<a href="/w/index.php?title=Rollin%27_with_Saget&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Rollin' with Saget (page does not exist)">Rollin' with Saget</a>" as the security guard, and in films such as <i><a href="/wiki/Training_Day" title="Training Day">Training Day</a></i> and <i><a href="/wiki/Soul_Plane" title="Soul Plane">Soul Plane</a>.</i>
</p><p>Crews usually portrays buff-looking characters with a humorous softer side. But more recently, he has been able to alternate with more serious projects such as his recent appearances in <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Harsh_Times&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Harsh Times (page does not exist)">Harsh Times</a></i>, <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Street_Kings_(film)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Street Kings (film) (page does not exist)">Street Kings</a></i>, and <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=The_Expendables_(2010_film)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="The Expendables (2010 film) (page does not exist)">The Expendables</a></i>.
</p><p>He has been featured in several <a href="/wiki/Old_Spice" title="Old Spice">Old Spice</a> TV commercials for their "Odor Blocker Body Wash", their body sprays, deodorant and most recently, their shaving lotion. The ads are directed by <a href="/wiki/Tim_Heidecker" title="Tim Heidecker">Tim Heidecker</a> and <a href="/wiki/Eric_Wareheim" title="Eric Wareheim">Eric Wareheim</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-oldspice_5-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-oldspice-5">[5]</a></sup>
</p><p>In the sitcom <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Are_We_There_Yet%3F_(TV_series)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Are We There Yet? (TV series) (page does not exist)">Are We There Yet?</a></i>, Crews had a lead role as Nick Kingston-Persons. In the series' first trailer, <a href="/wiki/Ice_Cube" title="Ice Cube">Ice Cube</a> said that Crews is the perfect person to replace him as Nick, and that his physical comedy is undeniable. The series was picked up for 90 new episodes<sup id="cite_ref-6" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-6">[6]</a></sup> (approx six seasons) by August 2010, while Crews enjoyed box office success in three movies in August 2010 (<i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Middle_Men_(film)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Middle Men (film) (page does not exist)">Middle Men</a></i>, <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=The_Expendables_(2010_film)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="The Expendables (2010 film) (page does not exist)">The Expendables</a></i>, <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Lottery_Ticket_(film)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Lottery Ticket (film) (page does not exist)">Lottery Ticket</a></i>).<sup id="cite_ref-7" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-7">[7]</a></sup>
</p><p>He also stars in his own reality series on <a href="/w/index.php?title=Black_Entertainment_Television&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Black Entertainment Television (page does not exist)">BET</a> entitled <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=The_Family_Crews&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="The Family Crews (page does not exist)">The Family Crews</a></i> which is about his everyday life with his family. The show premiered on February 21, 2010.
</p><p>In 2012, he joined the cast of the <a href="/wiki/Aaron_Sorkin" title="Aaron Sorkin">Aaron Sorkin</a>-helmed drama <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=The_Newsroom_(U.S._TV_series)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="The Newsroom (U.S. TV series) (page does not exist)">The Newsroom</a></i>. He will be portraying the bodyguard and <a href="/wiki/Life_coach" title="Life coach" class="mw-redirect">life coach</a> of Will McAvoy, the show's protagonist.<sup id="cite_ref-8" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-8">[8]</a></sup> There was a reference to his football past during his first appearance in the series, but the football past of his character, <i>Lonny Church</i>, is different from his real-life one. Terry was also a contestant in a <a href="/wiki/NBC" title="NBC">NBC</a> celebrity reality competition series called <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Stars_Earn_Stripes&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Stars Earn Stripes (page does not exist)">Stars Earn Stripes</a></i>.
</p><p>In July 2013, it was revealed that Crews is to play a real life version of the cartoon character used as the mascot for the group <a href="/w/index.php?title=Major_Lazer&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Major Lazer (page does not exist)">Major Lazer</a>, appearing in the video for their track, "Scare Me".<sup id="cite_ref-9" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-9">[9]</a></sup>
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Personal_life">Personal life</span></h2>
<p>Crews has four daughters, Azriel, Tera, Wynfrey, Naomi Burton, and one son, Isaiah, one grandchild (one being a stepdaughter from his wife's previous relationship) with his wife of 22 years, <a href="/w/index.php?title=The_Family_Crews&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="The Family Crews (page does not exist)">Rebecca King-Crews</a>, a former <a href="/wiki/Beauty_queen" title="Beauty queen" class="mw-redirect">beauty queen</a> and <a href="/wiki/Gospel" title="Gospel">gospel</a> <a href="/wiki/Recording_artist" title="Recording artist" class="mw-redirect">recording artist</a>.
</p>
